Citation.sTitle: Study of liquid liquid equilibrium of the systems isobutyl acetate + acetic acid +water and isobutyl alcohol + acetic acid +water at different temperatures
Citation.sAbstract: In this work, experimental liquid liquid equilibria (LLE) data of the systems isobutyl acetate + acetic  acid +water and isobutyl alcohol + acetic acid +water are presented. The liquid liquid equilibria of both  systems have been measured at 283.15 and 323.15 K. The NRTL and UNIQUAC models were applied to fit  the data for both ternary systems. The interaction parameters obtained from both models successfully  correlated the equilibrium compositions. The experimental tie lines were compared to the values predicted  by the UNIFAC method. Moreover, the solvent capabilities of isobutyl acetate and isobutyl alcohol  were compared.
